SIMPLE: instimulate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Instimulate
<hw>In*stim"u*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>stimulate</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not to stimulate;
to soothe; to quiet.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Cheyne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Instimulate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Instimulate
<hw>In*stim"u*late</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>instimulatus</ets>, p. p. <ets>instimulare</ets> to stimulate. See
1st <er>In-</er>, and <er>Stimulate</er>.]</ety> <def>To stimulate; to
excite.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Cockeram.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Instimulation</ent>⟦br⟧
